nodes.title: Info
widgets_values:
CLIP L: Keywords & Short Tags. This is the secondary encoder used to anchor the main subjects and simple concepts. Use concise terms here to stabilize the image structure.

CLIP G: Natural Language & Concepts. This is the primary, powerful encoder for SDXL. It understands complex descriptions, artistic styles, and fine details. Describe the scene's mood, lighting, and nuances here using full sentences.

Switch: 1 - Standard Clip G & Clip L / 2 - Both Clip G / 3 - Both Clip L / 4 - Swapped Note: Stick to 1 for the intended SDXL behavior. Swapping them usually degrades quality.
